<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Ragon der Magier:
[I]Hy, helix!

I앐 surely the first one to side you in the judgement on your observation.
To be fair, it is in fact not the case that you앏l "always look the same" regardless what equipment.
It압 just so, that [i]Larian Studios[/i] resorted to the "common standard" of, for instance, only reflecting changes between weapon or armor [i]classes[/i], like from leather to chain to plate and that for all (or most) body areas.
I agree vehemently with you if it comes down to [b]unique[/b] items, especially for the parts of the [i]Dragon Armor Set[/i] it would have been the least to do for [i]Larian[/i](=[b]mandatory[/b] >:)), giving that an accordingly [b]unique look[/b].

Yet, what you faced is [b]not a bug[/b], save a "major" one - it압 just sadly the reflection of concessions to a [i]significant lack of ressources[/i], time and manpower to name the most apparent.

At one point the [i]Larians[/i] had finally to shift attention towards fixing the still left cohorts of bugs, and even then the game got torn out of their hands and thrown into the market and theyre hunting the last ones to date, to recover from the impact a premature release had on  :div:압 success in Germany as far as can be overviewed.

I surely don앖 spoil a big secret if i state that, though in the very early days when still going under the working title "Project C", it was one design goal for  :div: to really reflect every single weapon or armor to be found in game also on the char압 sprite (contrarily to [i]Diablo[/i], e.g.).
But - too few graphics designers to do the paramount mass of animation frames that would have been required for that (there are 10 000+ for the Warrior already w/out that, anyway!) soon "rang the bell" for giving up on these ambitions.

One finally has to concede that we at least got [i]roofs[/i] for the game압 buildings instead, kind of in a [i]"last minute, last ditch"[/i] effort.
 ;)

Next game ( :div: 2!? :D), better luck,
gtx,
Ragon
 :)[/I][/QUOTE]

